{"title_page": "Robert Eziakor", "text_new": "{{Infobox football biography\n|name                = Robert Eziakor\n|fullname            = Robert Eziakor Chinedu<ref>http://espzen.com/teamPlayers_ex.asp?leagueNo=74&teamno=529</ref>\n|birth_date          = 19 October 1986\n|birth_place         = [[Onitsha]], [[Anambra State]], [[Nigeria]]<ref name=\"hgfc\"/>\n|position            = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n|years1              = 2006\n|clubs1              = [[Sporting Afrique]]<ref name=\"hgfc\"/>\n|years2              = 2007\u20132008\n|clubs2              = [[Katong FC]]<ref name=\"hgfc\"/>\n|years3              = 2009\n|clubs3              = [[Singapore Recreation Club]]<ref name=\"hgfc\"/>\n|years4              = 2010\u20132012\n|clubs4              = [[Tiong Bahru United FC|Tiong Bahru FC]]<ref name=\"hgfc\"/>\n|years5              = 2013\n|clubs5              = [[Hougang United FC]]\n|caps5               = 8\n|goals5              = 1\n|manageryears1       = 2013\u201320??\n|managerclubs1       = [[Hougang United FC]] (staff)\n|manageryears2       = 2016\n|managerclubs2       = [[Tiong Bahru United FC|Tiong Bahru FC]]<ref>http://www.fas.org.sg/sites/default/files/National%20Football%20League%202016%20Match%20Report%20-%20Stage%203%20%26%205%20%28M.15%20%26%20M.24%29.pdf</ref>\n|manageryears3       = 2017\u2013\n|managerclubs3       = [[Hougang United FC]] ([[Prime League]] and \nClub General Coordinator/Club Safety Officer)<ref>http://www.sleague.com/clubs-profile/hougang/club-profile</ref>\n}}\n\n'''Robert Eziakor''' (born 19 October 1986 in [[Onitsha]], [[Anambra State]], [[Nigeria]]) is a [[Nigeria]]n head coach and former footballer.\n\n==Career==\nPlaying for a host of Singaporean minor league sides,<ref name=\"hgfc\"/> Eziakor signed for [[Hougang United FC]] of Singapore's top division in 2013<ref name=\"hougang\">http://www.hgfc.com.sg/cheetahs-sealed-final-foreign-spot-with-robert-eziakor/</ref> and was handed the number 20.<ref name=\"hgfc\"/> Registering the most goals for his team in pre-season, he formed a good strike partnership with Guinean [[Mamadou M. Diallo|Mamadou Diallo]], aiming to be on the top scorers charts by the end of the season.<ref name=\"hgfc\">http://www.hgfc.com.sg/interview-with-robert-eziakor/</ref> During an interview, Eziakor maintained that it was difficult for him to get back into shape for professional football since he was less fit from plying his trade with semi-pro clubs.<ref name=\"hgfc\"/>\n\nThe forward has stated that he has enjoyed the vehemence and support of the Hougang HOOLS, his team's fan club during his time there.<ref name=\"hgfc\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Eziakor, Robert}}\n[[Category:Nigerian footballers]]\n[[Category:Nigerian expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Nigerian football managers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Singapore]]\n[[Category:Singapore Premier League players]]\n[[Category:Hougang United FC players]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n|name                = Robert Eziakor\n|fullname            = Robert Eziakor Chinedu<ref>http://espzen.com/teamPlayers_ex.asp?leagueNo=74&teamno=529</ref>\n|birth_date          = 19 October 1986\n|birth_place         = [[Onitsha]], [[Anambra State]], [[Nigeria]]<ref name=\"hgfc\"/>\n|position            = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n|years1              = 2006\n|clubs1              = [[Sporting Afrique]]<ref name=\"hgfc\"/>\n|years2              = 2007\u20132008\n|clubs2              = [[Katong FC]]<ref name=\"hgfc\"/>\n|years3              = 2009\n|clubs3              = [[Singapore Recreation Club]]<ref name=\"hgfc\"/>\n|years4              = 2010\u20132012\n|clubs4              = [[Tiong Bahru United FC|Tiong Bahru FC]]<ref name=\"hgfc\"/>\n|years5              = 2013\n|clubs5              = [[Hougang United FC]]\n|caps5               = 8\n|goals5              = 1\n|manageryears1       = 2013\u201320??\n|managerclubs1       = [[Hougang United FC]] (staff)\n|manageryears2       = 2016\n|managerclubs2       = [[Tiong Bahru United FC|Tiong Bahru FC]]<ref>http://www.fas.org.sg/sites/default/files/National%20Football%20League%202016%20Match%20Report%20-%20Stage%203%20%26%205%20%28M.15%20%26%20M.24%29.pdf</ref>\n|manageryears3       = 2017\u2013\n|managerclubs3       = [[Hougang United FC]] ([[Prime League]] and \nClub General Coordinator/Club Safety Officer)<ref>http://www.sleague.com/clubs-profile/hougang/club-profile</ref>\n}}\n\n'''Robert Eziakor''' (born 19 October 1986 in [[Onitsha]], [[Anambra State]], [[Nigeria]]) is a [[Nigeria|Nigerian]] head coach and former footballer.\n\n==Career==\nPlaying for a host of Singaporean minor league sides,<ref name=\"hgfc\"/> Eziakor signed for [[Hougang United FC]] of Singapore's top division in 2013<ref name=\"hougang\">http://www.hgfc.com.sg/cheetahs-sealed-final-foreign-spot-with-robert-eziakor/</ref> and was handed the number 20.<ref name=\"hgfc\"/> Registering the most goals for his team in pre-season, he formed a good strike partnership with Guinean [[Mamadou M. Diallo|Mamadou Diallo]], aiming to be on the top scorers charts by the end of the season.<ref name=\"hgfc\">http://www.hgfc.com.sg/interview-with-robert-eziakor/</ref> During an interview, Eziakor maintained that it was difficult for him to get back into shape for professional football since he was less fit from plying his trade with semi-pro clubs.<ref name=\"hgfc\"/>\n\nThe forward has stated that he has enjoyed the vehemence and support of the Hougang HOOLS, his teams fan club during his time there.<ref name=\"hgfc\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Eziakor, Robert}}\n[[Category:Nigerian footballers]]\n[[Category:Nigerian expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Nigerian football managers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Singapore]]\n[[Category:Singapore Premier League players]]\n[[Category:Hougang United FC players]]\n", "name_user": "John of Reading", "label": "safe", "comment": "Typo/generalfixes, replaced: teams fan \u2192 team's fan", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robert_Eziakor"}
